// absorbed from ~/core/hexa-matter/LIMIT_BREAKTHROUGH.md (MIT, hexa-matter v1.2.0, dancinlab 2026-05-14)
//
// compiler/atlas/materials_limits.gen.hexa — atlas @C rodata mirror of the
// real-limits anchored in hexa-matter's Wave-M audit. Mirrors the 12-row
// §2 table plus the per-limit numerical sub-rows from §3 (fibers, refractory
// melting points, thermal conductivity, concrete grades, packing fraction).
//
// SSOT for the source markdown: ~/core/hexa-matter/LIMIT_BREAKTHROUGH.md.
// Verbatim prose mirror: doc/atlas/materials_real_limits.md (BG-3 2026-05-14).
// This file is the structured/auditable accessor surface for the same data.
//
// Each row is an AtlasNode of kind "C" with:
//   id      — materials_limits.<slug>
//   raw     — header `@C <id> = <value> :: materials_limits.<sub_cat> [<grade>]`
//             plus continuation lines `formula:`, `value:`, `citation:`,
//             `class:` carrying the HARD_WALL / SOFT_WALL / BREAKABLE_WITH_TECH
//             / UNCLEAR taxonomy per compiler/lattice_policy/limit_class.hexa.
//   grade   — heuristic: HARD_WALL → 11, SOFT_WALL → 10,
//             BREAKABLE_WITH_TECH → 9, UNCLEAR → 7 (user-tunable).
//
// Regenerate via: hexa run tool/atlas_absorb_hexa_matter.hexa  (planned).
// Until that tool lands this file is hand-curated against the source MD.

use "compiler/atlas/parser"

@phase("parse_only")
